# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Warehouse14 mobile — environment template (committed; copy to .env for dev).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The app defaults to PRODUCTION (https://api.warehouse14.de) — a device build
# works out of the box against the live server. For LOCAL development against
# your own api-cloud, copy this file to `.env` and set the override:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is gitignored (it holds your Mac LAN IP, which is network-specific).

# Local api-cloud. The iOS Simulator reaches localhost directly. A physical
# device needs the Mac's LAN IP (e.g. http://192.168.1.42:3001) — or use
# `pnpm adb` on Android to map localhost on the device to the host.
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001

# (optional) Override the dev device fingerprint the app sends as
# x-dev-device-fingerprint. Defaults to the seeded dev device. Rotate it if you
# seed a new dev device via apps/mobile/dev/reset-dev-backend.sh.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_DEV_DEVICE_FINGERPRINT=71defad08503fcfb00b0b57e7654b3ed48afb264d34c69c3edb90a65a6b8f698
